    What are mute flowers?
    With the exception of rose, jasmine, tuberose, magnolia, narcissus, daffodil, mimosa, cassia, orange blossom, lavender, broom, ylang ylang and osmanthus, all other flowers are “mute”, meaning they release no extract that can be used in a fragrance, because the extraction yield is insufficient or simply inexistent.

    Are flower petals transparent?
    Petals are composed of layers of cells with air pockets between them. When dry, these air pockets scatter light, creating the flower's white appearance. Rainwater fills these spaces, eliminating the scattering effect and allowing light to pass through the petal, creating a glass-like transparency.

    Are skeleton flowers real?
    Diphylleia Grayi, also known as skeleton flower is native to northern and central Japan. Skeleton flowers appear white when dry and translucent when wet. They contain air pockets that reflect light. When it rains, the water fills the air pocket, and the flowers become translucent.15 Jan 2025
